40kadm5_ret_t
41kadm5_c_get_principals(void *server_handle,
42 const char *expression,
43 char ***princs,
44 int *count)
45{
46 kadm5_client_context *context = server_handle;
47 kadm5_ret_t ret;
48 krb5_storage *sp;
49 unsigned char buf[1024];
50 int32_t tmp;
51 krb5_data reply;
52
53 ret = _kadm5_connect(server_handle);
54 if(ret)
55 return ret;
56
57 sp = krb5_storage_from_mem(buf, sizeof(buf));
58 if (sp == NULL)
59 return ENOMEM;
60 krb5_store_int32(sp, kadm_get_princs);
61 krb5_store_int32(sp, expression != NULL);
62 if(expression)
63 krb5_store_string(sp, expression);
64 ret = _kadm5_client_send(context, sp);
65 krb5_storage_free(sp);
66 if (ret)
67 return ret;
68 ret = _kadm5_client_recv(context, &reply);
69 if(ret)
70 return ret;
71 sp = krb5_storage_from_data (&reply);
72 if (sp == NULL) {
73 krb5_data_free (&reply);
74 return ENOMEM;
75 }
76 krb5_ret_int32(sp, &tmp);
77 ret = tmp;
78 if(ret == 0) {
79 int i;
80 krb5_ret_int32(sp, &tmp);
81 *princs = calloc(tmp + 1, sizeof(**princs));
82 if (*princs == NULL) {
83 ret = ENOMEM;
84 goto out;
85 }
86 for(i = 0; i < tmp; i++)
87 krb5_ret_string(sp, &(*princs)[i]);
88 *count = tmp;
89 }
90out:
91 krb5_storage_free(sp);
92 krb5_data_free (&reply);
93 return ret;
94}
